  "prompt": "Why was the Pakistan national anthem sung first in the India-Pakistan World Cup match?",
  "response": "The Pakistan national anthem was sung first in the India-Pakistan World Cup match due to the established protocol and understanding regarding the order of national anthems during international sports events. Typically, when two teams from different countries compete, the anthem of the visiting team is played first. Since Pakistan was considered the visiting team at that match, their national anthem was performed before India's. This practice is common in sports to show respect to the visiting team.",
